==English==

===Etymology===
From Middle English ''[[sithe]]'', from Old English ''[[siththa]]'' both of which literally mean: "shadowed face" or "a face hidden in the shadows."  Hence, the connotation is one of secrecy and concealment.

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]]:/sɪθ/

===Preposition===
'''sith'''
# ''(Archaic)'' [[since]].

===Proper noun=== 
'''Sith'''

# ''(Star Wars)'' An ancient order of dark-side practitoners bent on power and passion instead of passive meditation, as opposed to [[Jedi]]. They are generally grotesque beings who cackle at inappropriate moments. See: [[Palpatine]]

